Text.Value: We're a team. I've got your back.
And spend every day looking over my shoulder? Waiting for someone to grab me and drag me back to the shadows?
I have to know. I have to face him.
And you will be with us when the time comes. It's fate, written in your very flesh.
Do you really think you can stop him?
Hold your tongue.
We should have killed them.
And if I can take this power from him, it would set me free. Truly free.
Why not stay away? Cazador can't finish the ritual if he can't find you.
You're not getting sentimental, are you? I thought you were with me on this.
Seven sigils on seven spawn, and Cazador has the other six. We have to face him and take that power for ourselves.
So let's do it.
He'll walk in the sun, he'll be free of the hunger, he'll wield power no vampire has ever possessed.
Isn't it obvious, sister? He wants to ascend with the rest of us.
Trust me, I'd rather slaughter someone else's family, but... if that's what it takes.
You owe your wretched life to my friend. Now tell me what I need to know.
And what if we're walking into a trap?
Why does Cazador need me? What is he planning?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Petra's close enough to the sunlight that he's starting to smoke

Text.Value: Fine.
The master is preparing the Black Mass. Beneath his palace. There's a defiled chapel - it was hidden there the entire time. Hidden from us all.
Then we'll deal with it! It can't be worse than everything else we've faced.
No, I won't spend eternity as a fugitive. I need to end this.
Where is he hiding? TELL ME.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Petra's close enough to the sunlight that he's starting to smoke

Text.Value: I'm the only one who can.
That's no way to welcome back a brother, Dal. Didn't you miss me?
Aren't you part of the sacrifice? Surely you'd be destroyed too?
Well yes, technically only I will ascend and gain the ritual's power.

EditorData.NodeContext: "Well yes, TECHNICALLY only I'll have all the power..."

Text.Value: Now go, before I change my mind about roasting you, brother.
This isn't over, Astarion.
You sound surprised - I am capable of doing the right thing from time to time.
Argh. ARGH!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Petra is starting to burn in the light

Text.Value: Who wouldn't be interested? It's the ultimate freedom.
Unless it's all a lie.
I am. More sure than I've ever been.
Yes, but only because of the parasite. This would be true freedom.
Freedom from the hunger, freedom to live a real life in the sun - no tadpole required.
Astarion, stop!
I want someone there, ready for me. And once the Mass is done and our lord grants us our freedom, I can celebrate by drinking them dry.
Then you'll help me in this. Nothing would make me happier.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion grabs Petra by the throat and drags him over towards the window. Standing full in the daylight, Astarion slowly pulls Petra closer and closer to the sunbeam.

Text.Value: I'm with you, no matter what.
We're here to kill Cazador. That's the only way you'll be free.
In fact, I'd be more powerful than ever. More powerful than any vampire has ever been.
It doesn't feel like a lie. It feels like exactly the kind of power Cazador would chase.
Well, it might be. And there's only one way to find out.
And you want what's best for me, surely?
Talk, or burn. Your choice.
The sun can't harm me, Cazador can't compel me. I don't need to fear him anymore.
The Black Mass - it will be his triumph. He'll complete the ritual and emerge the Vampire Ascendant.
Worst of all, they don't know their fate's already set. They're doomed.
Why thank you, darling.
You never liked following orders, brother. That's why you won't ascend with the rest of us.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] Custom anim: spawn freed himself from astarion

Text.Value: I knew I could count on you. We share that killer instinct.
The master is preparing the Black Mass. Beneath his palace. There's a defiled chapel - it was hidden there the entire time. Hidden from us all.
Perhaps, but it's a devils' deal. They always have some loophole or another.
Is that possible? For you to take his place?
If it was possible to take Cazador's place, you'd have to sacrifice the other spawn.
You sound interested.
We should go. I do not want to face the master if we're late for his Black Mass.
You heard them. Tell me what I need to know. Now.
Keep talking.
But we're a team. If I become all-powerful, then we become all-powerful.

EditorData.NodeContext: emphasis on "I" and "we", as if explaining to a child

Text.Value: What of it? You can already walk in the sun.
If you're sure...
Brother, please!
Can we go? We got what we need - the ritual's below the palace.
Best of all, we'll join him. His loyal servants - walking in the light as living vampires. We'll be free, brother.
What is Cazador planning? What do you know?
NO!
Say nothing.
It comes with a cost, yes. All great things do.
I'm glad you spared them.
We are a team, aren't we? You're still with me?
You can't believe that. You can't be that stupid.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion throws Petras away, releasing his grip on his throat. Petras and Dalyria revert to default positions in the dialog.

Text.Value: And if I were to ascend instead of him: freedom from Cazador, once and for all.
The Black Mass - it will be his triumph. He'll complete the ritual and emerge the Vampire Ascendant.
He's playing mind games. He can't raise a hand to the master, let alone kill him.
Soon, sister. I only need one more mark.
It's not for the master, it's for me. I spent one hundred years eating rats and dogs, but soon I'll be able to feast.
Of course that's why he came crawling back. He wants to ascend with the rest of us.
Perhaps, but if I don't confront him some day, I know I'll spend the rest of my life running from him.
And now we know that Cazador's skulking somewhere beneath the palace, it'll be infinitely easier to track him down.
The sun can't harm me, Cazador can't compel me. I'm the only person who can stop him.
What the hells happened to you, Astarion? What are you?
I'm not sure.
Don't get ahead of yourself - there's a lot we don't know.
But there's nothing to be afraid of - we're a team after all.
You can't mean that.

EditorData.NodeContext: startled, drops her voice to almost a whisper for "Kill the master", as if she's afraid her master will hear

Text.Value: I knew I could count on you. It's that killer instinct I love so much.
Poor fools. They actually think Cazador will save them...
Cazador promised you your freedom? And you believed him?
I'm going to stop Cazador.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion throws Petras away, releasing his grip on his throat. Petras and Dalyria revert to default positions in the dialog.

Text.Value: You were never burdened with intelligence, Petras, but your load seems especially light these days.
Astarion? It - it cannot be...

EditorData.logicalname: SET FLAG: KNOWS AST. IN CITY

Text.Value: Those six spawn are your brothers and sisters. Are you ready to sacrifice them?
You can't believe that, Dal. When has Cazador ever shared power?
Well figure it out. I need to know I can rely on you.
We deserve this, Astarion. Can't you see? We've given him everything - our blood and tears - and he's finally going to reward us.

EditorData.stateContext: Astarion is holding Petra by the throat, holding him near a sunny window

Text.Value: Yes. And they'll be trembling in fear when they tell him.
'For Ourselves'? For yourself, you mean.
I knew I was right about you. You're a true friend.

EditorData.stateContext: Both Vampire Spawn have left the scene

Text.Value: Still though, a living vampire...

EditorData.NodeContext: Contemplating just how good that would be

Text.Value: All right, let's go. This place stinks of rat blood and despair.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] Can use a construction for the turning

Text.Value: The only question is whether their lives will be sacrificed to a monster like Cazador or serve a greater purpose.
I'm more than what I was. And I'm not afraid of anything anymore.
Sometimes you scare me more than the elder brain does.
You always were an idiot, Petras.
And it's not like they're sweet innocents: they brought Cazador just as many victims as I did.
Tell me what I need to know, or I swear you'll burn.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vampire spawns turn to mist and vanish from the scene

Text.Value: Don't tell me what to do!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: turning to look at player over his shoulder while still holding Petra by the throat

Text.Value: They're no threat to us, and they have no choice but to do Cazador's bidding. I pity them.
Come on, time to leave.
And just think - I could rid myself of the mind flayers' parasite without losing anything.
And now that we know he's skulking beneath his palace, we can take the hunt to Cazador.
Why would you come back? You got out - you were free.
He'll walk in the sun, he'll be free of the hunger, he'll tap into power no vampire has ever dreamed of.
Best of all, we'll join him. His loyal servants - walking in the light as living vampires. We'll be free, brother.
You have no idea what I can do.
I just want you to be happy.
Just tell us about the ritual. What do you know?
They'll warn him we're coming.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion throws Petras away, releasing his grip on his throat. Petras and Dalyria revert to default positions in the dialog.

Text.Value: We have enough for the master - no more are needed.
He heard about the ritual and the power our master will grant us, so he came back with his tail between his legs, hoping all would be forgiven.
Besides, I'll need something to protect me from the sun if things don't work out with our parasite friends. This ritual could set me free.

Synopsis:
Dalyria and Petras at the flophouse.
They are looking for Astarion at the place where they used to "hunt".
This is a dialog for when they meet Astarion-companion with player-Avatar.
They will tell Astarion they must inform Cazador that Astarion is back in the city. They will also reveal that Cazador is planning a ritual that requires all the spawn and that will grant them new powers.
If the player & Astarion know that Cazador is actually planning to sacrifice all the spawn, he might be able to convince the spawn about this sacrifice. In exchange, they will reveal a bit of information about Cazador's Palace.
After the dialog they disappear as clouds of mist.
